good idea, and<br />never mind any barriers at all. The ordering for atomics really isn't<br />well enough specified that we should care. So I wouldn't object to a<br />patch that just removes the volatile entirely, but it would have to be<br />accompanied with quite a bit of testing, in case some odd case ends up<br />depending on it. But nothing *should* be looping on those things<br />anyway.<br /><br />                       Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
